quote_first: I'd really have liked to, I told her, if it weren't for the things I had in the dryer. I cast an eye at my watch.
quote_raw: I'd really have liked to, I told her, if it weren't for the things I had in the dryer. I cast an eye at my watch. One-twenty-five. The dryer had already stopped.
title: Hard-Boiled Wonderland and the End of the World
author: Haruki Murakami
